-Add in caret support to Spark List. Our default renderers draw a thin 1px blue line (same color as selection color) around items that are currently in focus.
-Selection and careted item stay in-sync unless the Ctrl key is down in which you can caret away on your own.
-With careting (current item in focus) comes the itemFocusChanged event.
-Add in more states to ItemRenderer, which now supports: normal, hovered, selected, normalAndCaret, hoveredAndCaret, selectedAndCaret.
-Because of the addition of a hasState() method on IStateClient2, IR's that don't support the above-mentioned states won't RTE!
-findKey support like in Halo, for Spark List
-Null check for Line when generating DAPI-2 stroke
Reviewers: Ryan for caret stuff, Ryan/Corey for hasState() impl
